AUDIO: 'This amazing fresh new AI work from NVIDIA&nbsp; just came out, and it is unbelievable,&nbsp;&nbsp; and can do the craziest things. My goodness, this&nbsp; is amazing. Okay, what’s going on here? Well,&nbsp;&nbsp; we have seen earlier AI-based works about text&nbsp; to motion. Writing a short prompt and then,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it makes a virtual character move accordingly.&nbsp; But I bet you haven’t seen this: what is this?&nbsp;&nbsp; This is called GENMO and it is not text to&nbsp; motion, no-no — this is everything to motion.'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'For instance, one, you can start out&nbsp; from a recorded video of yourself,&nbsp;&nbsp; and it learns and transfers those moves&nbsp; to a virtual character. That is crazy,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'because it has to look at 2D pixels, and convert&nbsp; them into moving around with joints and limbs&nbsp;&nbsp; in 3D. So we climbed the stairs, nice, now what?&nbsp; Well, two, now we want to do a lunge on one leg,&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but we are a bit lazy. Do you know what? Just&nbsp; add a text prompt and ask the AI to do it. This is incredible. But it gets better!'

